In this article, President Donald J. Trump proclaims June 2019 as African-American Music Appreciation Month. He pays tribute to the talented African-American artists who have contributed to various genres of music, including blues, jazz, gospel, rock and roll, rap, and hip hop. The article highlights the significant contributions of Aretha Franklin, an iconic African-American musician who recently passed away. President Trump encourages public officials, educators, and the people of the United States to observe this month by organizing activities and programs that raise awareness and appreciation for African-American music.